g.text: Logs everything which is inputted by other code. Depending on the level (DEBUG,
OPERATING, NONE) it saves it on a file (internal or external), in a buffer (only errors)
Handles all sensors and their data. It periodically polls the data and converts them if
needed e.g. the voltage of the temp sensor to a temperature. Its main purpose is to
collect their data and provide them if asked.
Handles files: Creating, Deleting, Saving, Writing etc. Internal (in the FLASH) and external
It manages the three SPI displays and their functionality. Furthermore it handles and
Center of the whole firmware. It initializes, configures and manages every other service. It
passes new data to the DisplayManager, instructs the FileManager and is the logical brain.
